faq_1.message: What is Tab Scheduler with Auto Open and Close?

faq_10.message: How do I view my scheduled tabs?

faq_11.message: Is it mandatory to fill in both the open and close times?

faq_12.message: What do the features of Auto Focus Tab, Activate All Scheduled Tabs, and Power Mode do?

faq_13.message: Can I open/close the schduled Website Link in incognito tab.?

faq_14.message: What is use of Refresh tab if URL is already open?

faq_2.message: What is the use of Website Link?

faq_3.message: How do I schedule a URL using Tab Scheduler?

faq_4.message: What is the 'Open URL in Background' option?

faq_5.message: Can I prevent the extension from closing pinned tabs?

faq_6.message: What does the 'Both' schedule type mean?

faq_7.message: How does the 'URL Filtering' feature work?

faq_8.message: Can I deactivate a scheduled tab without deleting it?

faq_9.message: Will I receive notifications for scheduled tabs?

faq_a_1.message: Tab Scheduler with Auto Open and Close is a browser extension that allows users to schedule tabs to open and close automatically at set times. Users can select a one-time schedule or set up recurring schedules with various frequency options. This extension has multiple purposes for users and provides many features that are helpful to you.

faq_a_10.message: All scheduled tabs are displayed in a list showing the title, website link, open and close times, status, and actions you can take (e.g., activate, edit, delete).

faq_a_11.message: No, you can schedule either an open time or a close time. However, you must fill out or select the required fields marked with an asterisk (*).

faq_a_12.message: Auto Focus Tab ensures that when a scheduled tab opens, Activate All Scheduled Tabs enables you to quickly turn on all your scheduled tabs with a single click. Power Mode optimizes the extension’s performance by managing browser resources more efficiently.

faq_a_13.message: Yes, you can choose to open a scheduled tab in incognito mode by selecting the "Open in incognito mode" option. You can choose to close only incognito tabs by selecting the "Close only incognito tabs" option, as long as "Allow in Incognito" is enabled in the extension settings

faq_a_14.message: When this option is enabled, the extension will automatically refresh an existing tab if the same URL is already open in your browser. This prevents opening duplicate tabs and ensures that you always have the latest version of the page loaded.

faq_a_14_1.message: If you try to open https://github.com/ and it’s already open in another tab, the extension will simply refresh that tab instead of opening a new one.

faq_a_14_2.message: If  https://github.com/ is already open in three tabs, the extension will refresh all three tabs.

faq_a_2.message: The Website Link is your browser's open tab website address. How you can use website address is mention below.

faq_a_3.message: To schedule a URL, enter the website link, give the schedule a title, select the frequency (One Time, Every Minute, Daily, etc.), and choose the open and close times. You can also specify a date, day, or seconds to open and close the tab.

faq_a_4.message:
This option gives you full control to schedule a URL to open in the background without bringing the new tab into focus. The URL will open quietly while you continue working on other tabs. It's particularly useful when you need the browser to fetch data from the scheduled URL without displaying it actively, such as in the case of a GET API request.


For example, if you want to fetch data from an API endpoint at a set time regularly, you can use this efficient option to run the request in the background without opening a new visible tab.

faq_a_5.message: Yes, there's an option to prevent the closure of pinned tabs. Check the "Do not close pinned tabs" option to ensure these tabs remain open even if they meet other closing criteria.

faq_a_6.message: The 'Both' schedule type gives you complete control over when a tab opens and closes, allowing you to set specific times for both actions.

faq_a_7.message: URL Filtering ensures that only a specific part of the URL needs to match for the scheduled action to take place. This is useful when you want to automate certain actions based on partial URL matches. For example, if you check the URL Filtering option for the URL https://example.com/page, it will also apply to URLs like https://example.com/page/123, https://example.com/page?query=example, and https://subdomain.example.com/page.

faq_a_8.message: With the "Activate this scheduled tab" option, you can easily activate or deactivate scheduled tabs, giving you the flexibility to manage your schedules without losing configurations.

faq_a_9.message: By default, you will receive notifications. However, if you prefer to stop notifications, you can check the "Do not show notification" option to disable them.
